Compensate Reps Based on Effective Territory Coverage Dates

This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Enterprise, Unlimited, and Developer editions. 

Territory assignment dates can differ from effective dates. For example, the assignment start date for a rep reflects when she joined the company on May 1. But she didnâ€™t assume ownership of her territory until her onboarding finished on May 31.

Track adjusted start dates, end dates, and reasons for any adjustments in custom fields or triggers that you add to the User Territory Association Logs object and any page layouts you create for it. Then give managers more insight for sales planning, equitable compensation, and analysis of sales performance when they report on that assignment data.
title: Compensate Reps Based on Territory Coverage Dates
